wrong scope is.

00:15:00.910 --> 00:15:03.130
And I actually did a little
bit of research into that.

00:15:03.130 --> 00:15:07.360
And it turns out that the
approval rates for apps that

00:15:07.360 --> 00:15:12.450
use a very restrictive scope,
like drive.file, is about 10%

00:15:12.450 --> 00:15:15.290
better, actually a little over
10% better than apps that

00:15:15.290 --> 00:15:18.080
request access to the
user's entire drive.

00:15:18.080 --> 00:15:20.360
And so users actually do pay
attention to this stuff.

00:15:20.360 --> 00:15:23.230
And it's important that when
you're building your app that

00:15:23.230 --> 00:15:25.370
you don't necessarily choose the
scope that's easiest, but

00:15:25.370 --> 00:15:27.670
you choose the one that's right
and reflective of what

00:15:27.670 --> 00:15:30.570
your app actually needs to do.

00:15:30.570 --> 00:15:33.010
